The Temporo-Mandibular Ligament attaches to the lateral aspect of the Temporo-Mandibular Joint (TMJ). 

Answer:  
{'cop': 'Lateral aspect of TMJ', 'cop_index': 0, 'why_correct': 'The temporo-mandibular ligament is attached to the lateral aspect of the Temporo-Mandibular Joint (TMJ).', 'why_others_incorrect': 'Options 1, 2, and 3 refer to different anatomical structures not involved in the attachment of the TMJ ligaments.'}

The Temporo-Mandibular ligament is a crucial structure that provides stability to the Temporo-Mandibular Joint (TMJ). It attaches to the lateral aspect of the TMJ, which refers to the outer or more rounded part of the joint. This attachment allows for effective support and movement during activities such as speech and mastication.

